==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Saddleback
<hw>Sad"dle*back`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Same as
<er>Saddle-backed</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Saddleback roof</b></col>. <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <cd>See
<cref>Saddle roof</cref>, under <er>Saddle</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saddleback</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Saddleback
<hw>Sad"dle*back`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Anything
saddle-backed; esp., a hill or ridge having a concave outline at the
top.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The harp seal.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>The great blackbacked gull (<spn>Larus
marinus</spn>).</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>The larva of a bombycid moth
(<spn>Empretia stimulea</spn>) which has a large, bright green,
saddle-shaped patch of color on the back.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saddle-backed</ent>⟦br⟧
